    {
      "parameters": {
        "content": "# Generate quotes with HTTP / REST API and Google Sheets\n\n**Pattern:** Document Generation · **Level:** Foundation · **Trigger:** Webhook\n\n## What it does\nGenerate quotes with HTTP / REST API and Google Sheets. It fires the moment an external system calls its webhook.\n\n## Why it exists\nManual invoices is slow and error-prone; this workflow makes the process repeatable, monitored and hands-off, with failures surfaced instead of silently lost.\n\n## Main flow\nReceive Inbound Webhook → Gather API Numbers → Blend Sources → Roll Up KPIs → Compose HTML Report → Send Report via Twilio → Save Execution Metadata → …\n\n## Use it for\n- Teams that want to document generation without manual effort\n- Anyone automating invoices in legal\n- Replacing a fragile manual process with a reliable workflow\n\n## You get\n- Keeps your systems in sync\n- Scales without extra headcount\n- Standardizes the process every time\n\n## Before first run\nConnect credentials: API key / bearer for the target API; Google OAuth2 / service account; Twilio SID + token.\nFollow the color key: 🟦 entry · 🟪 AI · 🟫 actions · ⬜ utilities · 🟩 outputs · 🟥 error rail.\nEach node has its own doc card underneath — read those before editing.",
        "width": 480,
        "height": 900
      },
      "type": "n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote",
      "typeVersion": 1,
      "position": [
        -830,
        80
      ],
      "id": "78e0b45e-e8d1-4296-a440-a50de1c3f1fc",
      "name": "📘 Workflow Overview"
    },
    {
      "parameters": {
        "content": "## 🔐 Security\n\nNever trust inbound payloads: the webhook path is unguessable. Add header auth or IP allow-listing for defense in depth. Secrets live in n8n credentials — never in node parameters.",
        "width": 360,
        "height": 260,
        "color": 1
      },
